WORDINDEX function

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| WORDINDEX(string, pos)                                                      |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

Returns the starting character position of the specified blank-separated word
in string.  If pos exceeds the number of words in string, a null string is
returned.

Examples:

	WORD('Now is the time',3) == 8
	WORD('Now is the time',6) == 0
